The '''Crispin asteroid field''' was an [[Asteroid/Legends|asteroid]] [[Asteroid field/Legends|belt]] located in the [[Crispin system/Legends|Crispin system]] in [[Wild Space/Legends|Wild Space]] of [[The galaxy/Legends|the galaxy]]. It contained [[Methane/Legends|methane]]-covered asteroids that were used as hiding places for [[Pirate/Legends|pirates]] and [[Smuggler/Legends|smugglers]]. The asteroid field and smugglers also both served as target practice for [[Mandalorian/Legends|Mandalorian]] [[Mandalorian Neo-Crusaders/Legends|Neo-Crusaders]] prior to the outbreak of the [[Mandalorian Wars]].

[[Canderous Ordo]] and his soldiers once accidentally freed what may have been a [[Yuuzhan Vong]] [[Yorik-stronha]] that had been frozen into one of the asteroids.

==Behind the scenes==
There is some debate as to what exactly was the object that the Mandalorians encountered in the asteroid field. While the description matches that of a Yuuzhan Vong coralcraft, some fans argue that it could not have been possible for a Vong ship to have made it to [[The galaxy/Legends|the galaxy]] four millennia ahead of the first scouting fleets, despite the presence of [[slivilith]] probes in the galaxy at that time.

"Crispin" was a character name written down in [[1973]] by the ''[[Star Wars]]'' franchise's creator, [[George Lucas]], during the early writing stages of<ref name="Making">''[[The Making of Star Wars: The Definitive Story Behind the Original Film]]''</ref> the first part of the [[original trilogy]], the [[1977]] film [[Star Wars: Episode IV A New Hope|''Star Wars'': Episode IV ''A New Hope'']].<ref name="YearByYear">''[[Star Wars Year By Year: A Visual History, New Edition]]''</ref>

